  "commit_message": "fix(client): restore OmitOpts default type to improve type-checking performance (#29592)\n\nFixes #29011\n\n<br/>\n\n## Problem\n\nAfter upgrading from Prisma 6 to 7, type checking on our production\ncodebase (406 models, ~9,300-line schema) became effectively unusable —\n`tsc --noEmit` ran for over 2 minutes and `tsgo` timed out at 3 minutes,\nwhereas it completed in ~9 seconds on v6.\n\nI traced this down to a single line change.\n\n<br/>\n\n## Root Cause\n\nIn #28375, the default value of the `OmitOpts` generic",
